tnam's future:\nmembers of the International Control Commission in Saigon have told an American embassy officer that all the Vietnamese they have met are anti-Diem. They believe the Viet Minh will inevitably take over free Vietnam since the free Vietnamese, in contrast to the Viet Minh, can count only on the \"ineffective, American-sustained Diem government\" or a combination of the sects sponsored by Bao Dai. The Viet Minh government and army represent the only real unity and strength in Vietnam.\n\nComment: The prolonged political crisis in the south has prevented the Diem government from starting an effective program that could appeal to the generally disillusioned public. At the same time, non-Communist members of the International Commission have invariably been impressed by the Viet Minh's effectiveness", "token_count": 131, "token_end_0based": 130, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "southeast asia 1 observers doubt free vietnam's future members of the international control commission in saigon have told an american embassy officer that all the vietnamese they have met are anti-diem they believe the viet minh will inevitably take over free vietnam since the free vietnamese in contrast to the viet minh can count only on the ineffective american-sustained diem government or a combination of the sects sponsored by bao dai the viet minh government and army represent the only real unity and strength in vietnam comment the prolonged political crisis in the south has prevented the diem government from starting an effective program that could appeal to the generally disillusioned public at the same time non-communist members of the international commission have invariably been impressed by the viet minh's effectiveness", "unred_source_page": 3}
